===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|yvel}}, {{m|enm|evel}}, {{m|enm|ivel}}, {{m|enm|uvel}}, from {{inh|en|ang|yfel}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*ubil}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*ubilaz}}<ref>{{R:gem:EDPG|*ubila-|page=557}}</ref> (compare {{cog|stq|eeuwel}}, {{cog|nl|euvel}}, {{cog|nds|övel}}, {{cog|de|übel}}, {{cog|got|𐌿𐌱𐌹𐌻𐍃|t=bad, evil}}), from {{inh|en|ine-pro|*h₂upélos}}, diminutive of {{m|ine-pro|*h₂wep-|*h₂wep(h₁)-, *h₂wap-|treat badly}}. Compare {{cog|sga|fel||bad, evil}}, from {{cog|cel-pro|*uɸelos}}<ref>{{R:cel:EDPC|head=*ufelo-|page=396}}</ref> and {{cog|hit|𒄷𒉿𒀊𒍣|tr=huwapp-<sup>i</sup>|t=to mistreat, harass}}, {{m|hit|𒄷𒉿𒀊𒉺𒀸|tr=huwappa-|t=evil, badness}}.<ref>{{R:hit:EDHIL|pages=369–370}}</ref>

Alternatively from {{m|ine-pro|*upélos||evil|lit=going over or beyond (acceptable limits)}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*upo}}, {{m|ine-pro|*h₃ewp-||down, up, over}}.

